casebody.data:
William R. JOHNSON, Respondent,
v.
TREASURER OF the STATE of Missouri-CUSTODIAN OF the SECOND INJURY FUND, Appellant. WD 81604 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: August 28, 2018 James E. Martin, Overland Park, KS, Attorney for Respondent. Joshua D. Hawley, Attorney General, and Kimberley R. Fournier, Assistant Attorney General, Kansas City, MO, Attorneys for Appellant. Before Division Four: Karen King Mitchell, Chief Judge, and Mark D. Pfeiffer and Cynthia L. Martin, Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

The Missouri Second Injury Fund (Fund) appeals from a Missouri Labor and Industrial Relations Commission (Commission) Final Award Allowing Compensation to William Johnson. Because there was sufficient competent evidence in the record as a whole to support the Commission's finding that Johnson reached maximum medical improvement on April 4, 2014, we affirm the Commission's award. Rule 84.16(b).
